OL,3,C'Rehash of dangerous system': Fears of
OL,4,COfsted's proposed grading scale
OL,6,F"But these proposals allow us to
OL,7,Fhighlight poor practice with more
OL,8,Fprecision ` pointing laser-like to
OL,9,Fspecific issues, not shining a
OL,10,Ffloodlight on the whole provider."
OL,12,FSir Martyn, chief inspector of Ofsted,
OL,13,Fsaid the death of Mrs Perry has been
OL,14,Fon his mind "ever since it happened".
OL,16,FHe said the "beauty" of a report card
OL,17,F` which he said is "a bit like a
OL,18,Fchild's school report card" ` is that
OL,19,Fit is different from the previous
OL,20,Fsystem in that it is "fairer" and
OL,21,F"more proportionate".
